Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:08.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Regarding the Hayase laboratory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.23,0:00:13.57,Main,,0,0,0,,We have identified a researcher we believe\Nwas involved in his core research.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:15.03,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.54,0:01:48.21,Main,,0,0,0,,"Disheartened Faraday"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:53.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.80,0:01:56.17,Main,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.76,0:02:00.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm banned from club activities for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.51,0:02:01.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Banned from the club?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.72,0:02:03.85,Main,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, I have to do these problems
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.85,0:02:04.06,Main,,0,0,0,,"Intermediate English\NProblems by Level"\N\N\NIn the meantime, I have to do these problems
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.06,0:02:07.69,Main,,0,0,0,,"Intermediate English\NProblems by Level"\N\Nand memorize all the\Nimportant vocab on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.69,0:02:08.35,Main,,0,0,0,,and memorize all the\Nimportant vocab on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.35,0:02:11.81,Main,,0,0,0,,It's nonsense! I'm out for a whole week!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.81,0:02:15.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, you did fail every\Nsubject on your quiz...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:19.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Even Mari only failed one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.11,0:02:20.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Stupid Hayase!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.87,0:02:23.33,Main,,0,0,0,,That traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:29.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Sis, is your nose itchy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:30.04,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.04,0:02:31.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Catching a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:33.75,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.75,0:02:36.21,Main,,0,0,0,,It's more like someone's\Nspreading rumors about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.21,0:02:37.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Rumors?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:42.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Darn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.60,0:02:45.72,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to study right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.72,0:02:47.47,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:49.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, give that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:51.85,Main,,0,0,0,,We have a tournament next week!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:54.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Which is more important, school or soccer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.94,0:02:57.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Soccer, duh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:02:58.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Soccer's #1!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:01.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm exhausted. You don't\Ncare about school at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:05.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm trying to become\Na pro soccer player.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:06.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't need to study!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:08.91,Main,,0,0,0,,A pro soccer player?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:11.42,Main,,0,0,0,,What team are you gonna join?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:13.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll join a J1 team, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.63,0:03:15.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:17.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Italy or France, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:19.51,Main,,0,0,0,,You dummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.51,0:03:22.05,Main,,0,0,0,,If you want to join a foreign team,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:24.39,Main,,0,0,0,,you need to know how to\Nspeak foreign languages!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.39,0:03:27.68,Main,,0,0,0,,English is the most basic of basics!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.68,0:03:31.44,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't even handle English,\Nbut you want to go to Italy? France?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.44,0:03:33.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't make me laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:37.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-Then... I'll just stick\Nwith a Japanese team.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:42.61,Main,,0,0,0,,And when you go overseas for the\NWorld Cup, what will you do then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.53,0:03:45.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see! I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:52.71,Main,,0,0,0,,You're not interested in being a good enough\Nplayer to be chosen for the World Cup, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.71,0:03:55.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I guess it's only natural\Nthat you suck at English.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.33,0:03:56.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Sh-Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.96,0:04:00.21,Main,,0,0,0,,You're only hurting yourself by not studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.21,0:04:03.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Studying should come first,\Nand soccer second!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:07.14,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with losing\Nyourself in what you love?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.06,0:04:09.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:17.73,Main,,0,0,0,,November 7th, 1872.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.73,0:04:22.36,Main,,0,0,0,,The Mary Celeste departed\Nfrom New York, heading to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:28.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Then, on December 4th, it was discovered\Nadrift in the ocean near Portugal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.53,0:04:30.45,Main,,0,0,0,,There was no sign of damage to the ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:33.87,Main,,0,0,0,,or of having being attacked by pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:39.04,Main,,0,0,0,,But the eleven people on board,\Nincluding the captain's family, were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:42.42,Main,,0,0,0,,No one knows what happened to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:44.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun! You're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:45.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:47.80,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:51.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Incidents of disappearances\Nall over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:55.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow... You like that kind of stuff, Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:04:57.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:04:59.40,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought these incidents and legends
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:03.44,Main,,0,0,0,,might have some connection\Nto Dr. Hayase's research.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.44,0:05:05.07,Main,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:06.78,Main,,0,0,0,,To Papa's research?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.78,0:05:07.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:11.91,Main,,0,0,0,,A man goes missing suddenly,\Nwithout explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:16.08,Main,,0,0,0,,If it's actually because he traveled\Nthrough time or dimensions...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:19.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Traveled through time? You mean, like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.29,0:05:21.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:25.34,Main,,0,0,0,,So if I investigate incidents of\Npossible time travel like these,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.34,0:05:28.51,Main,,0,0,0,,it's possible that I might learn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:34.52,Main,,0,0,0,,what the machine downstairs is, and why\NDr. Hayase gave you the armillary compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:39.02,Main,,0,0,0,,I think all this might be a message from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:41.94,Main,,0,0,0,,A message from Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:45.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Gilbert. Franklin. Volta.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:48.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Why do these people appear in this book?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:52.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Why are you traveling into\Nthe times they come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:59.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.21,0:06:00.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:01.75,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.75,0:06:03.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Please! Send me into the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:04.59,Main,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:07.09,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't mean the 16th or 18th centuries!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.09,0:06:08.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Just an hour or so ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:10.84,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:16.64,Main,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to make Futa mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:19.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I was just worried about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:20.60,Main,,0,0,0,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:23.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so stupid! Stupid! Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:25.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.44,0:06:28.65,Main,,0,0,0,,That's why... you have to send me back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.65,0:06:31.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me meet myself before I talk to Futa,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.16,0:06:33.83,Main,,0,0,0,,so I can tell me to be nicer!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:38.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.83,0:06:42.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?! Why do you have\Nthat armillary compass?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:44.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:45.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Didn't I mention it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:47.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I found it in the basement!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.71,0:06:49.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Why do you have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:53.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Well... with the way things were going...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:56.81,Main,,0,0,0,,It seemed like the right idea\Nat the time, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:58.39,Main,,0,0,0,,With the way things were going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:00.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm a member of Team Time Travelers, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:01.48,Main,,0,0,0,,"Team Time Travelers"\N\NI'm a member of Team Time Travelers, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:03.19,Main,,0,0,0,,"Team Time Travelers"\N\NI need an item of my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.19,0:07:03.77,Main,,0,0,0,,I need an item of my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:06.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Team Time Travelers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:09.53,Main,,0,0,0,,W-W-We'll talk about that some other time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.53,0:07:12.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, send me into the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.11,0:07:14.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Just an hour back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.37,0:07:16.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Listen, Waka.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.20,0:07:20.12,Main,,0,0,0,,The system doesn't let us\Ngo back whenever we want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.12,0:07:24.29,Main,,0,0,0,,We can only travel back to the eras\Nof the people in this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:36.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Lucky me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:37.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:41.52,Main,,0,0,0,,--Waka!\N--Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:51.11,Main,,0,0,0,,God wants it to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.11,0:07:54.66,Main,,0,0,0,,He wants me to go one hour into the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:08:00.12,Main,,0,0,0,,God, I will do as you ask of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.12,0:08:04.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Into the past... one hour ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.29,0:08:07.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Michael Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.13,0:08:12.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Lived from 1791 to 1867.\NFrom the 19th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.34,0:08:12.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.93,0:08:15.18,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't go that far back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:16.64,Main,,0,0,0,,It's no use, Waka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:19.47,Main,,0,0,0,,We can only go to the eras of the\Npeople written about in that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.47,0:08:22.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Then find a page with Futa Ichikawa on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.68,0:08:25.10,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't think there's a page for Futa...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.10,0:08:28.23,Main,,0,0,0,,How do you know unless you look?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.24,0:08:33.95,Main,,0,0,0,,What the heck?! They're all blank!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.95,0:08:36.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't be so reckless! You'll tear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:39.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't stop me, Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.08,0:08:40.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I told you to stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:53.47,Main,,0,0,0,,They both... traveled?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.59,0:08:55.55,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1821\N(What is now) London, England"\N\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.55,0:08:57.89,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1821\N(What is now) London, England"\N\N\NOw, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.89,0:08:58.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Ow, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:02.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Were you hurt, Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:03.39,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:06.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Where's Futa?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:08.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Where are we? The school?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:10.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.32,Main,,0,0,0,,This is clearly another country...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:14.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-Then, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:16.95,Main,,0,0,0,,We're probably in 19th century London.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:20.24,Main,,0,0,0,,The era of Mr. Faraday from the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:21.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.58,0:09:23.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait! What are we going to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.41,0:09:28.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Nineteenth-century London? In the\Nmiddle of the industrial revolution?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:29.63,Main,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:32.71,Main,,0,0,0,,When the time comes, we'll\Nreturn to our own time naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:33.88,Main,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:38.18,Main,,0,0,0,,And there's a way to get back\Nwithout having to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:39.43,Main,,0,0,0,,There is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.43,0:09:40.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:42.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa taught me before. See...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:45.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, my ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.57,0:09:59.03,Main,,0,0,0,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:00.37,Main,,0,0,0,,...a real hottie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.37,0:10:02.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Not that! He's... you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.99,0:10:04.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.66,0:10:06.62,Main,,0,0,0,,He's a hottie, but I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:08.79,Main,,0,0,0,,No, Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:10.79,Main,,0,0,0,,It's Mr. Faraday, the scientist!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:11.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:13.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:16.67,Main,,0,0,0,,You've heard of me? I'm delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:19.80,Main,,0,0,0,,To hear you refer to me as a scientist...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:22.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, would you get down from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:24.97,Main,,0,0,0,,You never know when the owner\Nof that cart will come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:26.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.39,0:10:29.69,Main,,0,0,0,,You two! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:30.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:31.52,Main,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.73,0:10:34.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Darn it! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:36.28,Main,,0,0,0,,We're sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:42.78,Main,,0,0,0,,You mean Dr. Hayase didn't cancel\Nhis research because it was a failure?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:44.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.03,0:10:47.25,Main,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, it was nearing completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.25,0:10:51.83,Main,,0,0,0,,But one day, Dr. Hayase suddenly\Ndeclared he was stopping his research,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:53.88,Main,,0,0,0,,and closed his laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:57.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. He gave me a high severance package
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:11:01.13,Main,,0,0,0,,and even recommended me\Nto a new place of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.13,0:11:07.22,Main,,0,0,0,,But he urged me not to say\Nanything about our research.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:11.60,Main,,0,0,0,,What kind of system was it?\NThe matter transporter...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.60,0:11:16.19,Main,,0,0,0,,It was a mysterious device. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:21.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Gambling is self-destructive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:23.99,Main,,0,0,0,,You should play in moderation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:31.50,Main,,0,0,0,,So, how was it mysterious?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:35.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, we managed to make an apple disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.59,0:11:38.55,Main,,0,0,0,,But we couldn't send it\Nwhere we wanted it to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:39.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:44.55,Main,,0,0,0,,But several minutes later, the apple\Nreturned to where it had been.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.55,0:11:46.35,Main,,0,0,0,,And it was rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.35,0:11:47.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Rotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:51.18,Main,,0,0,0,,After that, we stopped\Nthe research for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.18,0:11:54.02,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.02,0:11:57.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. You've been a great help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:00.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.74,0:12:02.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:05.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Some kind of accident must have occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:07.70,Main,,0,0,0,,during the development\Nof the matter transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.70,0:12:13.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Then someone resembling Hayase sent\Na jade cup of Napoleon to an auction
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.12,0:12:16.04,Main,,0,0,0,,to pay back his research funding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:20.38,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems it is necessary to take\Ncontrol of that laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.81,0:12:30.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.31,0:12:32.10,Main,,0,0,0,,You came here from the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.10,0:12:36.27,Main,,0,0,0,,and you met Franklin,\Nwho's even further in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.27,0:12:37.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:40.65,Main,,0,0,0,,You know the kite he used to prove\Nthat lightning is electricity?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.65,0:12:42.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:43.53,Main,,0,0,0,,How wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.53,0:12:45.66,Main,,0,0,0,,I wish I could have seen it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:46.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.78,0:12:50.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Aren't you at all suspicious of our story?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.33,0:12:51.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:55.71,Main,,0,0,0,,It sounds like an astounding dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.71,0:13:00.55,Main,,0,0,0,,But that just means science\Nhas turned a dream into reality!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:04.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Science... turns dreams into reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:08.18,Main,,0,0,0,,I believe in the greatness of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.18,0:13:13.39,Main,,0,0,0,,The truth is, the other day, I had a\Nsuccessful scientific experiment, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.39,0:13:17.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Today, I sent a thesis discussing\Nmy results to a publishing company.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.15,0:13:20.23,Main,,0,0,0,,--This will change our understanding\N--Hey, why can he speak fluent Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.23,0:13:24.11,Main,,0,0,0,,--of how electricity and magnetism relate.\N--He's not. We're speaking\Nfluent English, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:25.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:27.11,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't really get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.11,0:13:29.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Was that too complicated for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:32.91,Main,,0,0,0,,A picture is worth a thousand words.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.91,0:13:35.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'll show it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.54,0:13:41.75,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the Royal Institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:45.38,Main,,0,0,0,,It's my laboratory and my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:46.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:48.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir Davy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.26,0:13:52.93,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.93,0:13:57.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Did you put together the report\NI asked you for two days ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:14:00.98,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I was almost done...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.98,0:14:05.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Were you occupied by some other experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.28,0:14:06.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:07.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Actually, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.20,0:14:11.49,Main,,0,0,0,,You should just be doing what I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.87,0:14:13.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.96,0:14:19.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.08,0:14:22.25,Main,,0,0,0,,If you wait a moment,\NI'll put the report together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:25.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I'm going\Nto a play with my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:26.55,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:29.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Please turn it in first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:31.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:33.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:35.81,Main,,0,0,0,,It's been some time since we last spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.27,0:14:39.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Who are those girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:42.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh. They're my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.61,0:14:44.82,Main,,0,0,0,,They came here from far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.82,0:14:46.90,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope you'll be willing to hear them out...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:49.07,Main,,0,0,0,,What a vulgar display.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.91,0:14:52.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Uneducated men
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.03,0:14:54.99,Main,,0,0,0,,often gather vulgar people around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.42,0:15:05.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Who was that? They were so mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:09.13,Main,,0,0,0,,That's Sir Davy, my patron, and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.13,0:15:12.55,Main,,0,0,0,,His wife has always disliked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:17.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Uneducated... Did she mean you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.22,0:15:19.64,Main,,0,0,0,,That's what his wife calls me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.64,0:15:21.81,Main,,0,0,0,,But you're a scientist, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:24.77,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems that a scientist who can't do math
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.77,0:15:26.86,Main,,0,0,0,,is often the subject of great scorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:28.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.53,0:15:30.11,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't do math?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.11,0:15:30.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:32.57,Main,,0,0,0,,But you're a scientist!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.57,0:15:35.58,Main,,0,0,0,,I come from a poor blacksmith family.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.58,0:15:37.79,Main,,0,0,0,,I never went to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:41.71,Main,,0,0,0,,But how is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:45.04,Main,,0,0,0,,How can you be a scientist without math?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:46.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.21,0:15:48.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Why do I...? Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.42,0:15:51.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Studying math is the most\Nbasic of basics, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.72,0:15:54.18,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about math,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:56.10,Main,,0,0,0,,but I love science.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:58.26,Main,,0,0,0,,I can beat anyone for enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.26,0:16:01.23,Main,,0,0,0,,But... loving it isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.23,0:16:03.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Because I love it, I can lose myself in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.48,0:16:07.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I can have a successful experiment\Nand get people to acknowledge me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.23,0:16:09.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Science is all I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:11.86,Main,,0,0,0,,After all, even if I lack education,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:13.70,Main,,0,0,0,,I still have science.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.70,0:16:15.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Getting results in the field you love...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.41,0:16:18.37,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no greater joy than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:20.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Soccer, duh!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:24.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with losing\Nyourself in what you love?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.21,0:16:30.30,Main,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.30,0:16:33.72,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll show you the experiment\NI was talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.60,0:16:39.26,Main,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:41.02,Main,,0,0,0,,I call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.02,0:16:42.93,Main,,0,0,0,,...an electromagnetic rotation device.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:45.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Electromagnetic rotation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.11,Main,,0,0,0,,The wire rotates around the magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:50.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Rotates?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:51.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.65,0:16:54.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, without the power of wind or water,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.65,0:16:57.62,Main,,0,0,0,,with just the power of\Nelectricity and magnets!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:16:59.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Electricity and magnets?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:02.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Last year, Professor Oersted of Denmark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:07.50,Main,,0,0,0,,discovered that electricity\Nhad the power to move magnets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.50,0:17:11.96,Main,,0,0,0,,When you bring a compass close\Nto an electrified copper wire...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:16.80,Main,,0,0,0,,...the electricity and the magnet\Nclearly interact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:20.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir Davy and Dr. Wollaston
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:23.98,Main,,0,0,0,,were experimenting to create\Nan electric motor based on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:25.85,Main,,0,0,0,,but it didn't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:29.73,Main,,0,0,0,,So I decided to carry on their research!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:31.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:37.53,Main,,0,0,0,,If I put a compass here\Nand run electricity through it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:41.83,Main,,0,0,0,,The needle moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.83,0:17:43.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:46.37,Main,,0,0,0,,It moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.37,0:17:50.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I experimented with moving\Nthe compass around,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.50,0:17:52.59,Main,,0,0,0,,and noticed a certain principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:55.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, what are the needles doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:18:00.55,Main,,0,0,0,,It's like they're surrounding the wire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.55,0:18:03.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! They don't all turn the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.56,0:18:06.02,Main,,0,0,0,,They seem to surround it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:08.23,Main,,0,0,0,,This is what I think--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.06,0:18:11.48,Main,,0,0,0,,If we pretend this bottle of ink is the wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:14.07,Main,,0,0,0,,when I run electricity through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.07,0:18:20.45,Main,,0,0,0,,it releases its power in a certain direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:22.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Its power?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.20,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, magnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.20,0:18:28.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Magnetism?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.33,0:18:30.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, attention, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.29,0:18:34.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Magnets and an electrified copper wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:37.84,Main,,0,0,0,,When their powers interact,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.84,0:18:39.84,Main,,0,0,0,,what phenomenon will we see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:41.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's have a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:47.52,Main,,0,0,0,,It's moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:49.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:50.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:52.40,Main,,0,0,0,,See what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.40,0:18:55.28,Main,,0,0,0,,The power emitted by the wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:58.49,Main,,0,0,0,,and the power of the magnet\Ninteracting with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.49,0:19:00.45,Main,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.45,0:19:02.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I think I can see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:05.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Science is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:09.46,Main,,0,0,0,,The lightning rod reduced\Ndamage caused by lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.46,0:19:12.04,Main,,0,0,0,,And the voltaic pile...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.34,0:19:24.05,Main,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.48,0:19:38.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir Davy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.28,0:19:42.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I stopped by the publisher,\Nand they showed me this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.66,0:19:45.49,Main,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.49,0:19:47.83,Main,,0,0,0,,...the thesis I submitted today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:49.50,Main,,0,0,0,,You read it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:52.67,Main,,0,0,0,,This is an outrage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.67,0:19:53.96,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.96,0:19:57.00,Main,,0,0,0,,This is one of the experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:00.47,Main,,0,0,0,,that Dr. Wollaston and I carried out\Nto devise an electric motor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.47,0:20:02.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.13,0:20:06.01,Main,,0,0,0,,But you stopped the experiment, so I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.01,0:20:09.64,Main,,0,0,0,,When did I give you permission\Nto do experiments?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:11.85,Main,,0,0,0,,These experimental results and your thesis...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.85,0:20:15.06,Main,,0,0,0,,They're both stolen from our research!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:18.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir... Davy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:19.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:22.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? The time limit's up already?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.74,0:20:24.20,Main,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.20,0:20:26.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:28.45,Main,,0,0,0,,What do we do about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.45,0:20:31.87,Main,,0,0,0,,D-Don't ask me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.17,0:20:38.88,Main,,0,0,0,,An overload?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.88,0:20:41.38,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll be dealt with in\Nan appropriate manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:43.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Be prepared!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.01,0:20:45.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.39,0:20:46.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.39,0:20:50.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.65,0:20:56.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.77,0:20:58.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Where's Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.73,0:21:01.94,Main,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.70,0:21:08.41,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.41,0:21:10.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari? Where's Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.20,0:21:11.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.83,0:21:23.30,Main,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no, no, no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.30,0:21:25.59,Main,,0,0,0,,I came back by myself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:29.14,Main,,0,0,0,,It must have something to do\Nwith the system overload.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.14,0:21:31.43,Main,,0,0,0,,At this rate, Waka will...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.43,0:21:33.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:38.65,Main,,0,0,0,,If she just turns the dial on the armillary\Ncompass, she can come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.65,0:21:40.15,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.15,0:21:42.57,Main,,0,0,0,,And Waka knows that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.19,0:21:47.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I... I never told her...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.37,0:21:54.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:22:00.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you here for a cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:06.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.51,0:22:08.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.55,0:22:11.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Where did Mari go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:14.10,Main,,0,0,0,,She went back... by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.10,0:22:16.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Went back?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.14,0:22:17.64,Main,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.64,0:22:20.56,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't like this! Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.56,0:22:22.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.94,0:22:25.15,Main,,0,0,0,,\N\NMari!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.15,0:22:26.90,Main,,0,0,0,,"Faraday's Resolve"\N\NMari!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.90,0:22:29.07,Main,,0,0,0,,"Faraday's Resolve"\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:00.75,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.75,0:24:02.96,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"\N\NMari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.96,0:24:04.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.29,0:24:08.80,Main,,0,0,0,,You got to see a real Faraday Motor?\NI'm so envious!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.80,0:24:11.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's a motor?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.13,0:24:13.43,Main,,0,0,0,,It's true that electricity\Nmade it spin, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.43,0:24:14.39,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\NIt's true that electricity\Nmade it spin, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.39,0:24:18.72,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\NA Faraday Motor uses the relationship\Nbetween electric current and magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.72,0:24:23.39,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\N\Nto generate power in a certain direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.39,0:24:25.52,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\N\NWhat kind of power?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.52,0:24:29.03,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\N\NHave you ever heard of a man named Fleming?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.03,0:24:31.15,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\N\NI know that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.15,0:24:31.74,Main,,0,0,0,,"Magnetic field"\N"Electric current"\N"Mercury" "Battery" "Power"\N\N\NFleming's left-hand rule, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.74,0:24:33.91,Main,,0,0,0,,"Fleming's left-hand rule"\N"Power" "Magnetic Field" "Electric current"\N\N\NFleming's left-hand rule, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.91,0:24:38.08,Main,,0,0,0,,"Fleming's left-hand rule"\N"Power" "Magnetic Field" "Electric current"\N\NFleming gave us an easy way to understand\Nthe movement created by the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.08,0:24:41.20,Main,,0,0,0,,"Fleming's left-hand rule"\N"Power" "Magnetic Field" "Electric current"\N\Nbetween electric current\Nand the magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.20,0:24:41.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"Fleming's left-hand rule"\N"Power" "Magnetic Field" "Electric current"\N\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.71,0:24:44.33,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.33,0:24:48.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Place a magnet between two long metal rods.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.29,0:24:53.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Then place a short metal rod on top\Nand run electricity through them...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.47,0:24:55.84,Main,,0,0,0,,The rod moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.84,0:24:55.89,Main,,0,0,0,,The electricity is passing through\Nthe short rod to the right,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.89,0:24:59.10,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N\NThe electricity is passing through\Nthe short rod to the right,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.10,0:24:59.35,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N\N\Nand the magnet's field is pushing upward,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.35,0:25:02.14,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Magnetic field"\N\N\Nand the magnet's field is pushing upward,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.14,0:25:02.31,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Magnetic field"\N\Nwhich produces the power\Nto move the rod forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.31,0:25:05.73,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Power"\N"Magnetic Field"\N\Nwhich produces the power\Nto move the rod forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.73,0:25:07.27,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Power"\N"Magnetic Field"\N\N\NWow!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.27,0:25:11.19,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Power"\N"Magnetic Field"\N\N\NJust like Fleming's left-hand rule says!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.19,0:25:15.57,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Power"\N"Magnetic Field"\N\NThis setup is used in the motors\Nof many different machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.57,0:25:18.57,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric current"\N"Power"\N"Magnetic Field"\N\N\NAnd the vehicle that uses it the most is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.57,0:25:18.62,Main,,0,0,0,,And the vehicle that uses it the most is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.62,0:25:20.20,Main,,0,0,0,,...the maglev train!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.20,0:25:23.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! A next generation vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.41,0:25:25.16,Main,,0,0,0,,that moves at over 600 km/h!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.16,0:25:28.17,Main,,0,0,0,,It's much faster than high-speed rail!
